    process.stdout.write('\n\n');
    process.stdout.write('\x1b[0m');
    messages.push({ role, content });
  }
};

export { main };
```

In this updated version, the `main` function first checks if a conversation ID was provided as a command-line argument. If not, it generates a new UUID. It then checks if a conversation file exists for the given ID, and if so, loads the messages from that file.

During the conversation loop, whenever the user types "exit", the function writes the current conversation to a JSON file in the `data/conversations` directory, using the conversation ID as the filename.

To run the application with a specific conversation ID, use:

```
node index.js my-conversation-id
```

To start a new conversation, simply run:

```
node index.js
```

